Parliament, Thursday, 10 October 2019 – The Chairperson of the Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa), Mr Mkhuleko Hlengwa, will tomorrow pay a courtesy call to the Western Cape Provincial Scopa meeting. This follows a meeting that Mr Hlengwa had with the Chairperson of Scopa from the Western Cape Legislature, Mr Lulama Mvimbi. Mr Hlengwa hopes to make similar visits to other provincial legislatures in an effort of working together to deepen accountability and effectiveness in the interest of the public. Details are as follows: Date: Friday, 11 October 2019
	Time: 14h00
	Venue: Western Cape Provincial Legislature ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR MKHULEKO HLENGWA. For media enquiries, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8062
	Cell: 081 377 0686
